  "articleSummary": "This tutorial-style guide argues that local Docker environments are often overlooked security targets, exposing developers to risks like intercepted traffic and unprotected services. It emphasizes that Docker bypasses default firewall rules (e.g., UFW on Ubuntu) and recommends using private Docker networks for isolation, with tools like `ufw-docker` for host-network configurations. The article also covers secrets management (validating placeholders to prevent JWT token leaks) and monitoring via canary tokens, targeting developers who need practical, actionable fixes for everyday local development setups.",
